value.0:
The Fort Cystana Silver Dragon guards serve and protect the people, acting as the first line of defense against would-be villains and criminals.

This officer looks like she's keeping an eye out for adventurers...

Value.value: *the woman nods* Hail. Are you looking for work? The Duchy is looking for adventurers to cull the beastmen.
Their lair can be found due east, beyond the elven lands.
They sneak through the forests and the swamps to reach us, remembering our ages' old wars with them, even though we no longer reside just north of them.
Go into their lair and dethrone their current king. Bring back one of his totems and we'll reward you handsomely for your efforts.
That is one of the foul, demonic totems of the beastmen. Well done. Here is your coin, as promised.
*the woman nods* Greetings. If you are looking for more work to do, our friends in Barak Runedar suffer similar incursions from the beasts surrounding them. Perhaps they have a job for you.

Are you having trouble finding them? They are located east. Follow the road all the way to the bridge that crosses the Crystal River. Pass over the bridge and head north until you find the hills surrounding the Beastmire. You'll find their cave entrance there.

value.0: The Rangers are an elite branch of the Silver Dragons whom boast great skill in archery, tracking, and scouting. With the potential threats lurking in the wilderness surrounding the kingdom, they play a vital role in keeping the people safe.

Value.value: *the ranger seems to be watching those who come and go on the road*

value.0: The Everguard are a small cadre of paladins sworn to the protection of the Crown of the Kingdom of Kohlingen. In times of need it is not unheard of for them to be called upon to execute justice or to represent the Crown on the battlefield.

Value.value: We are here to ensure the Beastmen do not get any ideas.
